            <note xml:id="foot.f2"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1224.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">George Howard Darwin</ref> had been suffering with stomach problems (see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-8702.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from G. H. Darwin, [1 October 1873]</ref>); he was a fellow of Trinity College, Cambridge, working on geodesy (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_5933.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">ODNB</hi></ref>).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_317.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Henry Walter Bates</ref>.</note>
